description:
The deity or deities of content have blessed us this week with viral offerings from two of our favorite coo-coo for Cocoa Puffs lefty social media influencers: Rep. AOC, and elderly tech blogger Taylor Lorenz. Neither was afraid to let the crazy fall out of their face holes this weekend.

Rep. AOC declared that America was made to be destroyed. Keep in mind that when she isn't making Instagram videos, Rep. AOC has a side hustle in Congress. She is also on tour with Bernie Sanders, performing at rallies in cities that voted overwhelmingly for Kamala Harris, yet that billionaire-funded NGOs can only organize a fraction of to show up and call it a flex. In AOC and the NGOs' defense, however, they know that if they lie, they can count on most in the media to swear by it.

AO
title: Rep. AOC vs. Taylor Lorenz: Who said more batsh*t crazier stuff this weekend?

description:
There are right ways for politicians to reach the culture, and then there are derpy ways to do it. This past weekend provided us with a perfect contrast of the two styles. In the red corner, we had Donald Trump showing up at a UFC event. In the blue corner, Bernie Sanders wandered on stage during the middle of Coachella. On a related note, Trump is over bigly with the American people while Democrats have never been less popular or more culturally irrelevant.

Let's start with Trump. It's a familiar scene. He walks out. The crowd erupts in "USA" chants. He shakes hands with people. America is made great again. Bros proclaim "we are so f*cking back" on Twitter.

title: As Trump wows the UFC, Bernie Sanders goes on cranky old man rant at Coachella about the oligarchy
